        <div id="comment_body_43504909" class="comment-wrapper" data-points="4" data-reason="Interesting">
            <div class="comment-body"><blockquote><div><p>I just cringe at the thought of someone who's life was affected reading some of the comments in this discussion.</p></div></blockquote><p>Far more lives were affected by the lockdown than by the bombing itself. Who are these hypothetical "someone"s you speak of? The victims' families?</p><p>You can't predict an individual's reaction any more than I can -- I can only predict my own. I'll tell you this: Civil panic would be a horrible way to "honor" the death of one of my loved ones. Speaking only for myself -- the only person I <i>can</i> speak for -- I would find no offense, and perhaps even some small glimmer of comfort, in my community and country opting to follow the British war slogan: "Keep calm, and carry on".</p></div>
